\title{RTrace: Architecture Governance and Static Analysis for R Projects}
\description{
A static analysis and architecture governance platform for R projects and packages. RTrace scans R codebases for structural and architectural problems that style checkers and linters do not address, including layer/dependency-direction violations, circular module dependencies, project structure conventions, complexity hotspots, and common anti-patterns ('<<-', 'assign()', 'setwd()', hardcoded paths). Rules are declared in a versioned YAML configuration file and evaluated by an extensible rule engine, producing diagnostics that can be rendered as colored console output, 'JSON', or 'Markdown' for use in interactive development and continuous integration.
